v2.0.1 | Feb 23 2026:
[Fix] clean() operator precedence: { } grouping added to || / && conditions
      on clean rule + .info checks; prevents wrong branch activation
[Fix] clean() quarantine branch: rescan now uses clean_check=1 to avoid
      duplicate hit records; explicit re-quarantine on failure
[Fix] monitor_check() double ClamAV scan: removed unconditional scan before
      remote/local branch; each file now scanned exactly once
[Fix] monitor_check() YARA: _yara_filter_filelist() now called before
      scan_stage_yara() to skip files quarantined by ClamAV
[Fix] monitor_kill() guards empty $monitor_pid; prevents kill -9 on process
      group 0 when monitor.pid is missing
[Fix] quar_hitlist() quarantine_suspend_user now runs before mv so stat can
      determine file owner; matches quarantine() ordering
[Fix] quar_hitlist()/quarantine() replace $RANDOM filename suffix with file
      inode for deterministic, collision-free quarantine naming
[Fix] checkout() remove dead lcd $lcd from FTP heredocs; add return after
      file count limit; fix threshold 25 → 50 to match error message; use
      mktemp for temp file
[Fix] importconf template: 5 missing variables added (email_subj, scan_yara,
      scan_yara_timeout, scan_yara_scope, import_custsigs_yara_url) and 16
      hardcoded values changed to $variable expansion to preserve user
      settings across upgrades
[Fix] importconf inotify_sleep default was "30" but conf.maldet default is
      "15"; scan_tmpdir_paths was missing /var/fcgi_ipc
[Fix] install.sh version gate (1.5|1.6|2.0) removed; session, quarantine,
      and temp data now preserved regardless of version
[Fix] install.sh upgrade now preserves event logs from previous install
[New] test coverage for importconf variable preservation (12 tests)
[Fix] import_conf() remote config sourcing replaced with safe parser
      (_safe_source_conf) that validates each line is a simple variable
      assignment; rejects $(), backticks, semicolons, pipes in values;
      prevents remote code execution via compromised config server
[Fix] import_conf() config source order corrected: internals.conf now
      sourced before conf.maldet, matching documented loading order
[Change] import_conf() modernized: backticks to $(), $[] to $(()),
      quote variable expansions in cp/echo/cat commands
[Fix] -co/--config-option: validate values before sourcing; reject
      command substitution ($(), ``), semicolons, pipes, and other
      shell metacharacters in config values
[Fix] hookscan.sh: validate filenames from ModSecurity inspectFile;
      reject shell metacharacters, non-printable characters, and
      non-existent files before passing to maldet
[Fix] conf.maldet installed world-readable (0644); changed to 0640 to
      protect slack_token, telegram_bot_token, and email_addr from
      local user disclosure; also applies to conf.maldet.hookscan
[Fix] hex FIFO created with mode 666 (world-writable); changed to 600
      since only root's scanning process uses the FIFO
[Fix] conf.maldet: 8 comment typos corrected (grammar, inotify_cpunice
      default, inotify scheduling descriptions)
[Fix] email_subj relocated to conf.maldet for user configuration;
      internals.conf provides fallback default
[Fix] README.md config tables: added 28 missing variables across 4 new
      sections (General Options, Remote ClamAV, ELK Integration, and
      expanded Alerting/Scanning/Quarantine/Monitoring tables); corrected
      slack_channels default
[Change] usage_short() adds [--force] to -u/-d, [email] to -e, FILE to
      -m; moves YARA hint from -U to -co sub-note
[Change] usage_long() documents --beta flag for -d (version update)
[Change] CHANGELOG.RELEASE entry ordering synced with CHANGELOG; 5
      duplicate entries merged for succinctness
[Fix] cron.daily update failure logging was dead code: pipeline exit code
      was tail's (always 0) instead of maldet's; use PIPESTATUS[0] to
      capture maldet exit code, matching cron.watchdog pattern
[Fix] README.md config table: corrected variable names (slack_channels,
      telegram_bot_token, telegram_channel_id), defaults (email_alert=0,
      quarantine_clean=0, email_addr, inotify_cpunice=18), and paths
      (maldetect.last backup symlink, /usr/lib/systemd/system/ service unit)
[Fix] conf.maldet comment typo: -a|--al corrected to -a|--scan-all
[Change] Rocky 8/9 Dockerfiles: add curl to package list so
      get_remote_file() curl code path is exercised in CI
[New] test coverage for cron.daily update failure logging (2 tests)
[Fix] cron.daily flock lock leaked to backgrounded scans; switched to
      CLOEXEC command form (flock -n FILE "$0") preventing fd inheritance
[New] SHA-256 checksum verification for YARA-X binary download in
      Dockerfile.yara-x
[Fix] cron.watchdog version update (maldet -d) now runs regardless of
      signature update result; previously gated on sigup success
[Fix] README.md md5v2.dat format corrected to HASH:SIZE:{MD5}sig.name.N;
      SIZE field (file size in bytes) was missing from description
[New] test coverage for clean() YARA rescan path and YARA(cav) signature
      count display label (3 tests)
[Change] Rocky Linux 10 added to CI (9-target, was 8); Dockerfile.rocky10
      fixed for base image, coreutils conflict, optional package separation
[Change] scan_stage_yara() code duplication eliminated: extracted
      _yara_scan_rules() helper to consolidate text rules and compiled
      rules scan/parse blocks (~80 duplicate lines removed)
[Change] scan_stage_yara() caches YARA binary and --scan-list detection
      via _yara_init_cache(); eliminates repeated yara invocations every
      monitor cycle; cleared on config reload
[Change] scan() filters quarantined/unreadable files from YARA file
      list via _yara_filter_filelist() before passing to
      scan_stage_yara(); reduces wasted YARA invocations on files
      already handled by MD5/HEX/ClamAV stages
[Change] unused yarac binary discovery removed from internals.conf;
      yarac was discovered via command -v but never referenced in
      runtime code
[New] test coverage for YARA download validation and compiled.yarc
      validation (6 tests); exercises import_user_sigs() syntax checking
      and scan_stage_yara() compiled rules engine validation
[Fix] import_user_sigs() validates downloaded YARA rules with yr check or
      yara before installing to custom.yara; malformed rules are rejected
      with warning instead of silently breaking YARA scanning
[Fix] scan_stage_yara() validates compiled.yarc with test scan before use;
      cross-engine (yarac vs yr) or corrupt compiled rules are skipped with
      warning instead of causing scan errors
[Change] README.md documents ignore_sigs regex/substring matching behavior,
      hit prefix table ({MD5}/{HEX}/{SA}/{YARA}/{CAV}), YARA batch scanning,
      hookscan YARA config, and compiled.yarc path
[Change] copyright headers updated to 2026 across 10 source files
[Fix] CHANGELOG CI matrix corrected to 8-target (was 9-OS); added YARA-X,
      removed Rocky 10 and Ubuntu 22.04 not in CI; merged duplicate v2.0.1
      date blocks
[Fix] README.md cron_prune_days default corrected from 14 to 21
[Change] signature count display shows "YARA(cav)" qualifier when
      native YARA is disabled (scan_yara=0); applied in both sigup()
      and scan() output
[Change] usage_short() adds YARA scanning hint (-co scan_yara=1) as
      sub-note under -co option
[Change] legacy plain-text README replaced with pointer to README.md
[Fix] scan_stage_yara() dedup anchored with end-of-field regex to prevent
      substring false-positives (e.g., test.php matching test.php.bak);
      ERE metacharacters in file paths are escaped
[Fix] scan_stage_yara() per-file fallback (YARA < 4.0) uses sh -c
      wrapper to capture YARA exit code through cpulimit; captures
      highest non-zero exit code so rule syntax errors are logged
[Fix] clean() YARA rescan: post-clean verification now invokes
      scan_stage_yara() so YARA-only detections are re-verified; skip
      dedup during verification so surviving detections are re-detected;
      honor clean_check parameter in non-quarantine clean path
[Fix] scan_stage_yara() deduplicates hits against scan_session, preventing
      double-counted files when ClamAV and native YARA both detect the same
      file (report-only and quarantine modes)
[Fix] scan_stage_yara() stderr filter handles YARA-X "can't open" message
      format in addition to classic YARA "could not open"/"could not map"
[Fix] trap_exit()/clean_exit() now clean up YARA temp files ($tmpdir/.yara_*)
      on signal/interrupt, preventing temp file leaks during aborted scans
[Fix] hookscan.sh passes scan_yara to maldet --hook-scan so ModSecurity
      upload scanning can leverage YARA rules when enabled in
      conf.maldet.hookscan
[Change] scan_stage_yara() uses --scan-list for batch file scanning,
      reducing process invocations from O(N*M) to M+1; falls back to
      per-file scanning on YARA < 4.0; YARA stderr captured and logged
      via eout with "could not open" noise filtered; sh -c wrapper
      ensures accurate exit code capture under cpulimit
[New] YARA-X (yr) CI coverage: Dockerfile.yara-x with YARA-X v1.13.0
      exercises yr scan code path; YARA tests accept either yara or yr
[New] native YARA scanning: scan_yara=1 enables YARA as an independent scan
      stage using the yara binary (or yr from YARA-X); supports custom rules
      via custom.yara and custom.yara.d/ drop-in directory; scan_yara_scope
      controls rule overlap with ClamAV YARA; compiled rules via yarac
      supported; issue #392, #277, #239
[New] custom YARA rule infrastructure: custom.yara single-file and
      custom.yara.d/ drop-in directory for third-party rule sets (YARA Forge,
      Signature-Base); preserved across upgrades; import_custsigs_yara_url
      for remote rule import
[Fix] clamselector() logs warning when clamd test fails and falls back to local
      clamscan, instead of silently switching engines; issue #452
[Change] cron.daily prune uses find -delete instead of find -print0 | xargs rm -f;
      eliminates race condition and subprocess overhead; issue #430
[New] cron.daily explicit cPanel detection: parse /etc/userdatadomains for addon
      domain and subdomain document roots outside public_html, ensuring all hosted
      content is scanned; issue #268
[Fix] view_report() resolves "newest" and empty scan ID to most recent session
      before email and display logic, fixing --report "" user@domain.com failing to
      email the latest report; replace $EDITOR with cat for terminal output; use eout
      for error messages; issue #336
[Fix] panel alerts now include signature name alongside file path; rewrite hit
      parsing from fragile for/awk/grep loop to while-read with BASH_REMATCH regex
      for correct handling of paths with spaces and regex metacharacters; issue #426
[Fix] InterWorx get_panel_contacts() guard against empty master_domain preventing
      siteworx call with missing --login_domain; issue #426
[Fix] tlog line truncation: switch from byte-based tracking (stat -c %s + tail -c)
      to line-based tracking (wc -l + tail -n) to prevent mid-line truncation in
      monitor digest emails and inotify batch scanning; issue #227
[Fix] clamselector() no longer overwrites user scan_max_filesize config; signature-
      derived max filesize now stored in separate sig_max_filesize variable used only
      for ClamAV --max-filesize; issue #410
[Fix] Telegram Bot API URL missing required /bot prefix before token, causing all
      Telegram alerts to fail; issue #461
[Fix] get_remote_file() curl now uses -f flag to fail on HTTP 404/500 errors
      instead of saving error pages as valid content
[New] cron.watchdog weekly watchdog script for independent fallback signature
      updates when primary cron.daily is broken or stale
[New] install.sh installs watchdog to /etc/cron.weekly/maldet-watchdog
[New] test coverage for update mechanisms: get_remote_file, sigup, lmdup,
      cron update integration, and watchdog (22 tests)
[Fix] find_recentopts incorrectly escaping find options to the right of
      ( -mtime .. -ctime ); previously normalized by eval; issue #440, pr#442
[Fix] persist configuration value inotify_docroot between upgrades; issue #439
[Fix] monitor_check() clamd fatal errors (no reply from clamd) no longer treated
      as malware hits causing false quarantines; issue #454, #447
[Fix] upgrade install no longer kills inotify monitoring; use systemctl restart
      when systemd is available; issue #414
[Fix] cron.daily overlapping runs prevented with flock-based lockfile; issue #373
[Fix] quarantine.hist missing signature name in batch quarantine (-q SCANID);
      use grep -F for literal file matching instead of egrep regex; issue #399
[Fix] Slack alerting updated from deprecated files.upload API to
      files.getUploadURLExternal + files.completeUploadExternal; issue #458
[Fix] Slack and Telegram alerts now fire in monitor mode digest/daily reports,
      not just single-file scan alerts; issue #387
[Fix] unrecognized CLI arguments now return exit code 1 instead of 0; issue #366
[Fix] monitor_check() no longer launches clamscan/native engine with empty file list,
      avoiding unnecessary CPU usage during idle monitor periods; issue #459
[Fix] scan_ignore_user/scan_ignore_group with non-existent user/group no longer
      causes find to error out and return empty file list; issue #335
[Fix] replace ed dependency with tail/cat for inotify log and event log trimming,
      preserving file inode for inotifywait; ed no longer required for monitor mode;
      issue #308
[Fix] empty -regex expressions no longer cause find errors when --include-regex or
      --exclude-regex are not specified; issue #72
[Fix] ignore_file_ext, --exclude-regex, --include-regex, and ignore_paths prune
      broken after eval removal; convert from string variables with embedded quotes
      to bash arrays for correct find argument passing; issue #446, #438, #450
[Fix] md5_hash typo in quarantine clean path causing incorrect hash passed to clean()
[Fix] compat.conf suppress_cleanhit mapping had contradictory logic (always false);
      corrected to migrate old suppress_cleanhit to new email_ignore_clean
[Fix] maldet.sh init script syntax errors: missing semicolons between RETVAL=$? and
      conditional on lines 68 and 82
[Fix] replace predictable temp files ($RANDOM/$$) with mktemp across functions library
[Fix] cleanup_scanlist() hardcoded wrong path /var/lib/maldetect/tmp; use $tmpdir
[Fix] placeholder username in cPanel cpapi2 fallback in get_panel_contacts()
[Fix] sigup() swapped user_hex_sigs/user_md5_sigs variable assignments causing
      incorrect signature count reporting
[Fix] undefined $retry_sleep in clamd remote retry log messages; use
      $remote_clamd_retry_sleep
[Fix] break used outside loop context in get_remote_file(); replaced with return
[Fix] ignore_sigs file not created when both ignore_paths and ignore_sigs missing;
      elif changed to independent if
[Fix] inotify cpulimit block incorrectly referenced $scan_cpulimit instead of
      $inotify_cpulimit in monitor_init()
[Fix] importconf Slack scope reference updated from files:write:user to
      files:write, files:read
[Fix] $intfunc variable name typo in maldet error message
[Fix] install.sh GPL output missing v2 qualifier
[Fix] typo "orginal" corrected to "original" in usage_long() and man page
[Fix] missing ;; terminator before esac in maldet wildcard case
[Fix] quote critical variable expansions in mkdir/chmod/chown/rm/source commands
[Fix] replace deprecated which with command -v in maldet and install.sh
[Fix] HEX stdin mode (hexstring.pl) had swapped arguments causing scan failures
      when scan_hexfifo=0
[Change] modernize all backtick command substitutions to $() in internals.conf and
      install.sh
[Change] update copyright headers to 2025 across all files (hexfifo.pl, hexstring.pl,
      maldet header(), install.sh output)
[Change] unify domain references from r-fx.org to rfxn.com across all file headers
[Change] rewrite usage_short() and usage_long() with categorized sections, complete
      option coverage (-co, -U, --web-proxy, -h), argument placeholders, and
      consistent formatting; replace runtime variables with literal text
[Change] version bump to v2.0.1
[New] cron.daily Bitrix panel detection (/opt/webdir + /etc/nginx/bx); issue #381
[New] BATS test infrastructure with Docker CI; 17 test files covering install/CLI,
      MD5 scanning, HEX scanning, quarantine, ignore files, config options, cron,
      reporting, signatures, file list generation, string length analysis, logging,
      purge, compat.conf migrations, hook scanning, resource control, and version
[New] GitHub Actions CI workflow with 9-target matrix: CentOS 6/7, Rocky 8/9/10,
      Ubuntu 20.04/24.04, Debian 12, YARA-X
[New] test coverage for clean operations, ClamAV integration, cron daily, and
      alerting (4 new test files, ~40 tests)
